The vote will take place early next week.
US lawmakers caused a gap in talks over the approval of the bailout plan in its form of aid to the US financial system in the amount of 700 billion dollars (about 12 trillion crowns).
However, he is not yet won.
Congressmen must fine-tune some details of the contract before they can make public the final form of the bill and have it voted on.
The plan to help the financial system will be discussed on Monday in the House of Representatives.
Barney Frank, chairman of the Assembly's Committee on Financial Services and Banking, told Reuters on Sunday.
According to some sources, the vote on the plan could be held in the Senate no earlier than Wednesday.
According to economists, the ratification of the bailout plan should mark the announcement of a first psychologically significant factor for the revitalization of the financial market.
The Commission has already made a number of proposals to this effect.
The plan must be effective.
"We have made great progress.
We resolved our divergent views on how the package of measures for market stabilization should be structured", said Democrat Nancy Pelosi to Bloomberg.
The Commission has not yet adopted a decision on the proposal.
Representatives of the legislators met Sunday night with the finance minister, Henry Paulson, to give a definitive shape to the government's fund.
It should buy from financial corporations the unsold mortgage assets that drive financial corporations into heavy losses and threaten the stability of the whole system.
"We are about to close the agreement on the plan, which will work and must also be effective in the market.
It is necessary to continue with the sanitation plan, but I think we are already at it", said Paulson.
A signal for Asian business
