Mrs. Boyd said it more simply: "Zora saved Eatonville".
The victory over the road project has helped change the image of the city itself.
People from out of town like Rachelle Munson, a lawyer who started coming to the church here in 1993, started showing up in large numbers, and residents started checking the past.
Eatonville was listed on the National Register of Historic Places in 1998.
