The life of this woman who marked a dance and aesthetic revolution in Europe between the wars, fascinated Isabel Bayón.
"I wanted to work with Pepa Gamboa and she proposed this character to me and I thought it was amazing".
According to the dancer, "we do not intend to tell his life but to collect his spirit.
The titles of their dances have given me the impression of flamenco sticks.
So, "butterfly dance" suggested a guajira, or "serpent dance" some tangos.
Her dance was sensual and I was told that my dance is also within this aesthetic", she says.
The installation features two exceptional collaborations: that of Miguel Poveda who will sing again to Isabel in one of his shows, as he did in "La puerta abierta"; and with the teacher Matilde Coral, who exceptionally wanted to collaborate with whoever was his student.
"Matilde plays Tortora as an adult, the character of maturity.
