Drivers who have a history of alcoholism must install an alcohol lock
Interior wants drivers with three administrative penalties for alcoholism to have to install a system in their vehicle that prevents them from starting the vehicle drunk, or if they don't blow.
The initiative was announced last June and is now included in the annual report of the State Attorney General's Office, which says it is a pilot project that will last for a year.
The purpose of this is to reintegrate the driver, so that he will also receive a road re-education course.
In addition to the General Traffic Safety Office, the Directorate General of Traffic (DGT) and the Institute of Technology for Automobile Safety Foundation (FITSA) will also participate in the experience.
According to statistics, between 30 and 75 percent of drivers who are reported more than once for drunk driving re-enter the car.
The alcolock would prevent this as it is a system connected to the vehicle that measures the alcohol rate in exhaled air and prevents the car from starting if the driver does not blow off the bottle; or when an alcohol concentration is detected is higher than the permitted.
The cost is more than 1,000 euros and would be borne by the person who was sanctioned.
In this respect, a 2007 study in the USA showed that vehicles equipped with these devices reduce infringements by up to 65% in the first year of deployment.
And in Spain it is estimated that it could save 115 lives every year.
The measure is based on administrative sanctions for two reasons: to address such behaviour before it leads to criminal offences.
And to facilitate its implementation, since the legal reform can be done by ordinary means, and, however, the necessary reform by the criminal means requires a reform in an organic law.
The device is not yet available on the Spanish market in any commercial form, although it has already been experimentally implemented in some industrial and public service vehicles.
The Commission has already taken a number of steps to ensure that the Community's own resources are used for the financing of the projects.
